4 A BILL FOR AN ACT ENTITLED: “AN ACT REVISING LAWS RELATED TO DRIVING UNDER THE
5 INFLUENCE; CREATING THE CRIME OF AGGRAVATED VEHICULAR HOMICIDE WHILE UNDER THE
6 INFLUENCE; PROVIDING PENALTIES; AND AMENDING SECTIONS 44-15-103, 46-18-201, 61-8-1007, 61-8-
7 1008, AND 61-8-1016, MCA.”
8
9 BE IT ENACTED BY THE LEGISLATURE OF THE STATE OF MONTANA:
10
11 NEW SECTION. Section 1. Aggravated vehicular homicide while under the influence. (1) A
12 person commits the offense of aggravated vehicular homicide while under the influence if the person
13 negligently causes the death of another human being while the person is operating a vehicle in violation of 61-
14 8-1002(1)(a), (1)(b), (1)(c), or (1)(d).
15 (2) Aggravated vehicular homicide while under the influence is not an included offense of
16 deliberate homicide as described in 45-5-102(1)(b).
17 (3) A person convicted of aggravated vehicular homicide while under the influence shall be
18 imprisoned in a state prison for a term of not less than 3 years or more than 30 years or be fined an amount of
19 at least $10,000 not to exceed $50,000, or both. Imposition of a sentence may not be deferred.
